# Activity Log Guard Rail

When you complete **substantive work** on this project, append an entry to `docs/ACTIVITY_LOG.md`.

## When to update

Update the log when you:

- Add or change a **feature** (UI, API, behavior)
- Fix a **bug** that affects behavior or correctness
- **Refactor** non-trivial code or rename important symbols
- Change **config** (env, build, Next.js, Supabase, etc.)
- Change **schema** or SQL (tables, migrations)
- Add or change **docs** that affect how the project is used or run
- Do a **chore** that future maintainers should know (e.g. adding this rule)

Do **not** log: trivial typo fixes, comment-only edits, or formatting-only changes.

## Entry format

Add **one entry** at the **top** of the "Entries" section in `docs/ACTIVITY_LOG.md`:

```markdown
### YYYY-MM-DD — `type` — Short summary

- **Summary:** One-line description.
- **Details:** (optional) Key files, API/schema impact, breaking changes.
```

**Type** must be one of: `feature` | `fix` | `refactor` | `config` | `schema` | `docs` | `chore`.

## Example

```markdown
### 2025-02-18 — `feature` — Export candidates to Excel

- **Summary:** Added export button on Candidates page that downloads filtered rows as .xlsx.
- **Details:** `app/candidates/page.tsx`, `lib/export-utils.ts`; uses `xlsx` package.
```

Keep entries brief. One log update per logical change (or batch of related small changes).
